Resolution statements support efficient retrieval through multiple indexes:

```
Indexing Architecture:
├─ Query ID Index → Rapid resolution lookup by query
├─ Timestamp Index → Chronological access for recent gathering
├─ Parent Relationship Index → Child resolution collection
├─ Claim Reference Index → Evidence linkage optimization
└─ Execution History Index → Performance analysis support
```

### Caching Strategy

Frequently accessed resolution statements are cached for performance:

```
Caching Optimization:
├─ Hot Resolution Cache → Recently accessed statements
├─ Relationship Cache → Parent-child relationship data
├─ Claim Link Cache → Frequently referenced claim connections
└─ Performance Cache → Resolution success patterns
```

## Quality Assurance

### Resolution Validation

System validates resolution statements for completeness and consistency:

```
Validation Checklist:
├─ Required Fields Present → query_id, intent, timestamp
├─ Parent Relationship Valid → Verified parent query exists
├─ Claim References Accurate → All referenced claims exist
├─ Tool Execution Complete → All referenced tools executed successfully
├─ Confidence Score Reasonable → Within expected ranges
├─ Impact Description Clear → Logical connection to actions
└─ Timestamp Consistent → Chronological order maintained
```

### Consistency Checking

Cross-resolution consistency is maintained through validation:

```
Consistency Validation:
├─ Claim Resolution Consistency → No contradictory claim usage
├─ Parent-Child Relationship Validity → Circular dependency prevention
├─ Timeline Consistency → Logical temporal progression
├─ Success Rate Tracking → Resolution pattern analysis
└─ Impact Assessment Accuracy → Reasonable impact descriptions
```

## Error Handling and Recovery

### Resolution Generation Errors

```
Error Management:
├─ Incomplete Data → Use available information, note gaps
├─ Missing Claims → Proceed without claim references
├─ Tool Execution Failures → Document errors, continue resolution
├─ Confidence Calculation Errors → Use conservative estimates
└─ System Timestamp Issues → Manual override with approximate times
```

### Context Assembly Errors

```
Recovery Strategies:
├─ Resolution Unavailable → Skip to next available statement
├─ Context Window Overflow → Intelligent truncation with key point preservation
├─ Index Failures → Linear search fallback
├─ Relationship Errors → Proceed without resolution linking
└─ Performance Issues → Reduce resolution count temporarily
```

## Success Metrics

### Effectiveness Metrics

```
Performance Indicators:
├─ Resolution Completion Rate: Percentage of queries generating resolution statements
├─ Context Relevance Score: Semantic similarity between context and current query
├─ Lineage Accuracy: Correctness of parent-child relationship tracking
├─ Claim Integration Rate: Percentage of resolutions referencing relevant claims
├─ Context Quality: Effectiveness of context in supporting query resolution
└─ System Efficiency: Time and resource consumption for context assembly
```

### Usage Analytics

```
Analytics Tracking:
├─ Resolution Statement Volume: Number generated per time period
├─ Context Hit Rate: Frequency of context informing successful resolutions
├─ Claim Reference Patterns: Most commonly referenced claims
├─ Tool Usage Trends: Frequently used tools in resolutions
├─ Query Resolution Speed: Time to resolution with context vs. without
└─ User Satisfaction: Perceived quality and usefulness of context
```

